The paper discusses the performance of parameter-reduced variants of LSTM RNNs on benchmark datasets, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with sentiment analysis (IMDB dataset) and text classification (20 Newsgroup dataset), which are tasks related to natural language processing (NLP). Hence, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the MNIST dataset, which is a popular dataset for image classification, indicating a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) as well. Finally, since the paper discusses the suitability of these networks for online training and inference on portable devices, it could also fall under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
